<b>Standard OS Textbook</b>
</big><br>
<p>
It would be very good to have one of the following at your disposal.
<ul>
<li>Silberschatz, Galvin, and Gagne.<br>
<cite>Operating System Concepts.</cite>
Seventh Edition, 2005.  John Wiley.<br>
(Or the sixth edition, if you don't mind remapping the TOC.)
<p>
<li> A. Tanenbaum.<br>
<cite>Modern Operating Systems (2nd Edition).</cite> 
Prentice-Hall, 2001.
(The substantially different first edition is also useful.)
</ul>
<p>

